          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Fairness For Breastfeeding Mothers Act of 2017</b></p> <p><strong></strong>This bill requires that certain public buildings that are open to the public and contain a public restroom&nbsp;provide a lactation room, other than a bathroom, that is hygienic and is available for use by members of the public to express milk. The lactation room must be shielded from view, be free from intrusion, and contain a chair, a working surface, and (if the building is&nbsp;supplied with electricity)&nbsp;an electrical outlet. </p>]]></text>
